Henceforth

26
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:56,630
the procedures of
Kunti province will be followed.

27
00:02:58,610 --> 00:03:00,590
If the platter has a variety
of tastes

28
00:03:00,610 --> 00:03:02,680
the joy of having food
increases, Prince.

29
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:07,640
If the tastes of here, Gandhar
and Kunti province join

30
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:09,490
what harm can it pose?

31
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:13,590
Don't try to preach to me!

32
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:18,600
You don't have the right
to offer me counsel.

33
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:23,690
I'm just trying to ease your
agitated heart, Prince.

34
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:29,610
I understand that you
are still disturbed.

35
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:33,660
But, Prince, the pillar
of a temple is as pious

36
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,480
as the stoup it holds.

37
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:38,560
As a matter of fact, the stoup
can't be without a pillar.

38
00:03:38,580 --> 00:03:40,560
The one who was born
to be considered the'stoup'

39
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,620
could never be
the supporting 'pillar'.

40
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:45,560
And the 'pillar' meant
for support

41
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:47,600
wouldn't suit if it were
glorified to be the'stoup'.

42
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:51,560
Which stone has been
made for either of them

43
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,590
is something only the architect
knows best about.

44
00:03:57,600 --> 00:04:01,480
We should accept the decision
of the Almighty, Prince.

45
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:05,650
This is the time to forego
of all bitterness

46
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,750
and welcome Pandu and Kunti.
- Don't touch me!

47
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:12,620
I haven't yet given you
the right to do so!

48
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,710
Every time...

49
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:20,450
Every time I try to
consider you as my wife

50
00:04:20,590 --> 00:04:23,540
this very behaviour of yours
makes me feel

51
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,530
as to how much
my insult...

52
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,730
Gladdens you.

53
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:28,670
How very much are
you at peace by the same!

54
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,570
Remember, Gandhari

55
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:37,470
Pandu's welcome
will neither be done by me

56
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:39,480
nor by you.

57
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:42,650
I am your husband.

58
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:45,480
My orders define your
rules of conduct.

59
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:50,520
Now whether you abide by
the same or not

60
00:04:51,590 --> 00:04:54,500
is a choice I leave to you.

61
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,710
Two persons

62
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,540
on coming closer

63
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:13,530
try to form boundaries and rules
for the other for sure.

64
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:17,640
If we ponder over every
relationship, we'd notice

65
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,520
that the source of all of them

66
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:25,530
are the very boundaries
that we draw for others.

67
00:05:25,590 --> 00:05:29,560
And even if unknowingly,
a stranger oversteps the bounds

68
00:05:29,590 --> 00:05:30,620
the very instant

69
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:34,510
our heart palpitates with anger.

70
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:38,580
What's the actual form of
these boundaries?

71
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,550
Have we ever given
it a thought?

72
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:43,540
By imposing boundaries

73
00:05:43,570 --> 00:05:46,670
we don't allow the other
to decide for himself.

74
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,640
We impose our decision
on the other.

75
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:54,720
In other words, we reject
the independence of another.

76
00:05:56,620 --> 00:06:00,590
And when independence
is rejected, his heart

77
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:02,560
is filled with sorrow.

78
00:06:02,690 --> 00:06:05,610
And when he breaks
all the boundaries

79
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,730
our heart is filled with wrath.

80
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:11,570
Isn't that how it always
happens?

81
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:20,520
But if everyone respects
the independence of another

82
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:25,510
boundaries and rules
become extinct.

83
00:06:25,550 --> 00:06:26,570
In other words

84
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:30,650
just like agreement is
the body of a relationship

85
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:35,600
isn't independence the soul
of a relationship?

86
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,700
Think over it.

87
00:06:50,570 --> 00:06:51,600
No, dear.

88
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,610
Son-in-law

89
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,670
the first to be offered respect

90
00:06:55,710 --> 00:06:58,720
is the King of the Yadavas
Shoorsen.

91
00:07:01,620 --> 00:07:03,610
He is the one who
sired Kunti.

92
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,500
No!

93
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:07,750
Greater than the father

94
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:10,720
is the one who
brings up the child.

95
00:07:10,730 --> 00:07:12,720
You are so right, sire.

96
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:16,670
The one who forsook one's
child after its birth

97
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:20,500
can never be the first
to be offered respect.

98
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:23,680
Your right will always
come second.

99
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,650
You may please proceed.

100
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,480
Please come.

101
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:10,560
Did you hear that, Priyamvada?

102
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:17,490
So generous and broad
is the outlook of my husband!

103
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:22,730
By selecting such a husband

104
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:27,740
I have made myself fortunate!
- Yes, Princess.

105
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:31,700
But now you must do
no such thing

106
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,710
that robs you of your fortune.

107
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:43,690
But I can't deceive my husband.

108
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:47,490
If in order to gain something
one has to lie

109
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,720
that's deception

110
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:54,430
but in order to shield oneself
from harm, if truth is concealed

111
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,570
it's not termed
a deception, Princess.

112
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,710
Don't try to weave
a web of words, Priyamvada.

113
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:06,510
The truths of the world

114
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:10,550
are but hazy at best
to palace dwellers

115
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:12,560
but do remember

116
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:16,560
that if the same truths
pass into the hands of a foe

117
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:18,610
they become but
trebuchets.

118
00:09:27,730 --> 00:09:30,460
What...
What are you doing?

119
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,700
This is a shield, Princess.

120
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:36,450
To safeguard your
and King Pandu's happy life

121
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:38,540
from the attacks
of any vile person.

122
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:43,560
Till the time this thread
is tied around your wrist

123
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:45,490
you won't say a thing

124
