00:17:17,710 --> 00:17:19,840
All hail!
- King Pandu!

220
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,660
Why did you stop, Adhirath?

221
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,820
The Chief Minister is coming
to welcome you, Your Highness.

222
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:37,810
Greetings!
- Greetings, younger brother!

223
00:17:37,870 --> 00:17:39,860
Greetings!
- Greetings!

224
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:41,840
His and Her Highness
are welcome.

225
00:17:42,970 --> 00:17:45,700
Your Highness, Mother Queen
has ordered

226
00:17:45,910 --> 00:17:48,950
that you should first pay
a visit to the district deity.

227
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:51,910
Won't you welcome your brother
and sister-in-law, Vidur?

228
00:17:52,850 --> 00:17:54,710
I would welcome
sister-in-law

229
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,780
by being her charioteer.

230
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:00,880
Adhirath, if you may,
please proceed to your home.

231
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,870
Please take some rest.

232
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:11,720
My lord!
My lord!

233
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:16,970
Radha, how are you?
Where is Karna?

234
00:18:17,710 --> 00:18:19,900
He is busy preparing for
the King and Queen's welcome

235
00:18:20,710 --> 00:18:22,780
so that Their Highness
be pleased.

236
00:18:22,780 --> 00:18:24,880
What are you saying?
Why didn't you stop him?

237
00:18:31,690 --> 00:18:34,850
My lord, how could I stop
him from welcoming the King?

238
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:37,880
God knows what kind
of welcome he would arrange!

239
00:18:38,690 --> 00:18:39,870
He won't use a bow
and arrows, right?

240
00:18:45,770 --> 00:18:47,930
You just don't understand
the gravity of any situation!

241
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:49,940
Now I have to stop him!

242
00:18:50,870 --> 00:18:51,810
Where is he?

243
00:18:53,710 --> 00:18:54,780
Lord Surya

244
00:18:54,810 --> 00:18:56,680
I don't know of any mantra

245
00:18:57,710 --> 00:19:00,960
but please bless my arrows
with the speed of light.

246
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:03,950
May no one be harmed by these.

247
00:19:55,740 --> 00:19:56,840
'These are
the very same flowers'

248
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:03,680
'in whose golden colour reside
the light of Lord Surya and'

249
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:08,860
'countless memories of mine.'

250
00:20:10,820 --> 00:20:13,820
Vidur, who showered
these flowers?

251
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:16,750
Such an amazing display
of archery!

252
00:20:17,690 --> 00:20:18,800
Who did this?

253
00:20:18,930 --> 00:20:21,810
This archer has
really pleased me!

254
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:23,710
Who is this archer?

255
00:20:23,870 --> 00:20:24,860
Come forth!

256
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,860
You deserve the thanks
of mine and the Queen!

257
